content:
From: clefort <ipub@charter.net>
Hello,

When I start up GNU emacs from the command line in terminal I get
this report at the bottom of the emacs window concerning ProofGeneral:

./bin/Isabelle

File `/Users/clintonlefort/ProofGeneral/generic/proof-autoloads.elc'
was not compiled in Emacs

What does this mean?

CL

From: Primrose.Mbanefo@Infineon.com
Hi clefort,

The second section on the FAQ on the Proof general website concerns that
topic :
http://proofgeneral.inf.ed.ac.uk/FAQ

In essence, you'll have to recompile for Emacs. I've done it once or
twice and it normally doesn't have any glitches.

Primrose
